<section class="gp-section" id="what">
  <h2>How Masseter Botox (Jaw Slimming) Works</h2>
  <p>Botulinum toxin injected into the <strong>masseter muscle</strong> (the large jaw muscle responsible for chewing) temporarily blocks nerve signals, causing the muscle to relax and gradually shrink in size over 4–8 weeks. The result is a slimmer, more oval face shape — sometimes called a "V-line" effect in Korea.</p>
  <p>It is particularly effective for people who:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Have naturally large masseters (genetic or from teeth grinding)</li>
    <li>Grind their teeth (bruxism) — jaw slimming also reduces grinding pain</li>
    <li>Want a softer, more oval facial contour without surgery</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The procedure takes 5–10 minutes. No numbing is needed for most patients. Results are not immediate — the muscle gradually reduces over 4–8 weeks with full effect at around 2–3 months.</p>
</section>

